          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Targets withstanding high beam power were developed",
                "using electrodeposition of Ga/Ni alloy (70/30%) on",
                "thick Cu backings."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "nuclide": "31-GA-69",
                "field_identifier": "NAT",
                "value": 0.60108
              },
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "nuclide": "31-GA-71",
                "field_identifier": "NAT",
                "value": 0.39892
              },
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV",
                "EXTB",
                "EDEG",
                "GSPEC",
                "MOSEP",
                "STTA"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The cross sections",
                "were measured using a stacked foil irradiation",
                "followed by non-destructive g-ray spectrometry. The",
                "targets were Ga-Ni alloy (70/30%) deposited with the",
                "electroplating technique on Au (thickness 25 um, for",
                "deuteron experiment) on Cu (12.5 um, proton",
                "experiment) foils as backing. The nominal thickness of",
                "the Ga-Ni layer was 17.3 um (deuteron experiment, 6",
                "mg/cm2 Ga) or 13.2 um (proton experiment).",
                "For 50 MeV deuteron the stack",
                "composed from 22 Ga-Ni targets on Au backing and Al",
                "and Ni monitor/degrader foils. The stack for proton",
                "irradiation consisting of 20 Ga-Ni alloy on Cu backing,",
                "interleaved with Tl/Cu degraders was irradiated with a",
                "36MeV proton beam. Decay data were taken from NUDAT",
                "online data library."
              ]
            }
          ],
